siness sector to survive in the face of corporate growth, the history of the industry on the Coast and in the Interior, the transformations in capital-labour relations during the period, government forest policy, and the forest industry's encounter with the emerging environmental movement are all considered in this eloquent analysis. With its critical historical perspective, Capital and Labour in the British Columbia Forest Industry will be essential reading for anyone interested in the business, natural resource, political, social, and labour history of the province.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBritish Columbia -- Economic conditions -- 20th century. 0aForest products industry -- British Columbia -- Employees -- Labor unions -- History. 0aForest products industry -- British Columbia -- History. 0aForest products industryxEmployeesxLabor unionszBritish ColumbiaxHistory. 0aForest products industryzBritish ColumbiaxHistory. 0aForesterie -- Colombie-Britannique -- Histoire. 0aForests and forestry -- British Columbia -- History. 0aForests and forestryzBritish ColumbiaxHistory. 0aProduits forestiers -- Industrie -- Colombie-Britannique -- Histoire. 0aProduits forestiers -- Industrie -- Colombie-Britannique -- Personnel -- Syndicats -- Histoire. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485516740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774855167423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774855167/original  a978-3